To install XAMPP on Ubuntu using the terminal, follow these commands

Step 1: Update the system
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y

Step 2: Download XAMPP with terminal commands
https://downloads.apachefriends.org/xampp-files/8.2.12/xampp-linux-x64-8.2.12-0-installer.run

 
Step 3: Make the installer executable
chmod +x xampp-linux-x64-8.2.12-0-installer.run

Step 4: Run the installer
sudo ./xampp-linux-x64-8.2.12-0-installer.run

Final step : Start XAMPP
sudo /opt/lampp/lampp start

Stop XAMPP:  
sudo /opt/lampp/lampp stop
